quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  2,142,"The fools among men will say, \"What has turned them from their Qiblah (direction, focus, goal), to which they were used?\" Say, \"Allah´s is the East and the West, He guides whom He will unto the Straight Way"
  2,143,"Thus have We made you a middle (or justly balanced) nation, to be witnesses against men, and that the Apostle may be a witness against you. We have not appointed the Qiblah (direction, focus, goal) which you were used to, save that We might know (test) wh"
  2,144,"We see you often turn your face towards the heavens, but We will surely turn you to a Qiblah you shall like. Turn then your face towards the Sacred Mosque (Kaaba in Mecca); wherever you are, turn your faces towards it; for verily, the People of the Book"
  2,145,"And even if you should bring to the People of the Book every sign, they would not follow your Qiblah (direction, focus, goal); and you are not to follow their Qiblah; nor do some of them follow the Qiblah of the others: and if you follow their lusts (vain)"
  2,146,"Those whom We have given the Book know this as they know their own sons, although a sect of them does surely hide the truth which they themselves know"
  2,147,"The truth (is) from your Lord; be not, therefore, one of those who doubt"
  2,148,"Every sect has a huwa (goal) to which Allah turns him; but do you strive onwards together to do good works; wherever you are Allah will bring you all together; verily, Allah has power over all things"
  2,149,"From wherever you come forth, there turn your face towards the Sacred Mosque, for it is surely truth from your Lord; Allah is not unmindful about what you do"
  2,150,"And from wherever you come forth, there turn your face towards the Sacred Mosque, and wherever you are, turn your faces towards it, that men may have no argument against you, save only those of them who are bent on wickedness; and fear them not, but fear"
  2,151,"Thus (similarly) have We sent amongst you an apostle from yourselves, to recite to you Our signs, to purify you and teach you the Book and wisdom, and to teach you what you did not know"
  2,152,"Remember Me, then, and I will remember you; thank Me, and do not disbelieve (or reject faith)"
  2,153,"O you who do believe! Seek aid from sabr (patience, perseverance, self-restraint and constancy) and from prayer, verily, Allah is with the patient"
  2,154,"And say not of those who are slain in Allah´s Way (the Way of striving, sacrifice and restraint) (that they are) dead. Nay, they are living; but you do not perceive it"
  2,155,"We will try you with something of fear, and hunger and loss of wealth, and lives and fruits (of toil); but give good tidings to those who patiently persevere"
  2,156,"Who, when there falls on them a calamity say, \"Verily, we are Allah´s and, verily, to Him is our return"
  2,157,"These are they on whom are blessings from their Lord and Mercy, and they it is who receive Guidance"